article.headline: Xavier 75, Dayton 67
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- Drew Lavender had 27 points and led the way as Xavier shot 51 percent from the field to beat Dayton 75-67 on Saturday night. Lavender, a 5-foot-7 transfer from Oklahoma, made 7-of-10 shots from the field including 5-of-7 3-pointers and also hit all eight of his free throws. Justin Doellman added 11 points and Stanley Burrell had 10 for the Musketeers (21-7, 11-3 Atlantic 10). Charles Little scored 28 points and had 10 rebounds for Dayton (16-11, 6-8). Brian Roberts chipped in with 14 and Andres Sandoval 10. The Flyers fell to 14-2 at home, and are 1-0 on neutral courts and 1-9 on the road. The Musketeers hit 11-of-24 3-pointers to Dayton's 3 of 9. They hit 8 of 12 in the opening half while building a 36-29 lead, and led by as many as 12 in the second half.
